This story is that of a British vet with 3 tours in Ulster under its belt.  He has lost mates and is suffering from PTSD.  The anti-American comments and moments are from his point of view.  As Fitz says, understandable but not justified.  I find the other reviewers a bit thin skinned.  If they had complained about the believability of the vet going off the rails, that would have been more valid in my opinion.
Not that bloody awful if you watch the whole thing
